  <!-- Section: Common Mistakes -->
  <section id="mistakes" class="scroll-mt-24 mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Common Mistakes to Avoid</h2>

    <div class="space-y-6">
      <div class="border-l-4 border-red-500 pl-4">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Insurance Too Short</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">Your insurance must cover the full visa duration (1-2 years). Monthly nomad insurance that can be cancelled won't work—you need proof of committed coverage.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="border-l-4 border-red-500 pl-4">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Underestimating Income Proof</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">The $3,000 threshold is firm. Showing $2,900 average won't cut it. If you're close, wait until you can demonstrate consistent $3,000+ income.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="border-l-4 border-red-500 pl-4">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Missing Apostille</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">Police clearance must be apostilled. Many countries require you to do this through your Secretary of State or equivalent. It adds 1-2 weeks to prep time.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="border-l-4 border-red-500 pl-4">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Applying for Wrong Visa</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">The Rentista visa (passive income) and Digital Nomad visa are different. Make sure you're applying for the DN visa if you have employment income vs. investment income.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="border-l-4 border-red-500 pl-4">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">No COVID Coverage</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">Costa Rica requires COVID coverage in your health insurance. Most modern policies include it, but verify before applying.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="border-l-4 border-red-500 pl-4">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Expecting European Internet</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">Internet in beach towns can be inconsistent. Research connectivity in your target area. San José area has best infrastructure.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

